<title>BRAZIL: Brazil gov't wins key civil service reform vote.</title>
<headline>Brazil gov't wins key civil service reform vote.</headline>
<dateline>BRASILIA 1997-07-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Brazilian government defeated a key amendment to its civil service reforms Wednesday, getting one more vote than the minimum necessary to kill the amendment that would have scuppered its reform, officials said.</p>
<p>Michel Temer, President of the Chamber of Deputies, said 309 deputies voted against an opposition proposal that would have prevented the authorities from firing workers for incompetence. He said 181 voted for the amendment and five abstained.</p>
